Task1
Write a function named solution that takes a single argument, number, which is a positive integer.
The function should return the sum of all natural numbers below number that are multiples of 3 or 5.
For example, calling solution(10) should return 23, because the natural numbers below 10 that are multiples
of 3 or 5 are 3, 5, 6, and 9, and their sum is 23.